The paper deals with interpreting deep learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The specific focus on assigning importance to individual neurons in a network suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), where understanding the internal workings of neural networks is particularly important.
